						<span>Introduction of Course</span><br/><br/>
							Information Technology is the field of study, design, development, implementation, support and management of computer-based information systems, particularly software applications and computer hardware. Generally, information technology helps to create, control, store, communicate, and circulate information.<br/><br/>
						
						<span>Demand and Career Prospect of Bachelor of Technology (IT) Course</span><br/><br/>
							The information technology sector continues to be one of the shining and fast growing sectors of the Indian economy. The ever-increasing IT sector provides unlimited job opportunities in India as well as abroad. The export constituent of Indian IT industry is likely to cross Rs. 8000 crores by the year 2020. Additionally, the domestic markets are likely to bring in supplementary returns of Rs. 10,000 crores during the next decade. All thanks goes to the success of the IT industry which has made India, an established power all over the world.<br/><br/>
							
						<span>Eligibility Criteria</span><br/><br/>
							To get Admission at CGC Landran- Best College for IT Engineering in Punjab then you must have 10+2 with Math and physics are compulsory subjects along with one of these subjects: computer science, bio-technology, biology and chemistry are eligible to pursue this B.Tech course. <br/><br/>
						<span>Admission Procedure</span><br/><br/>
							Admissions will be done on the basis of JEE rank for Punjab Domiciles and for students belonging to other states through online counseling conducted by PTU, Jalandhar. 66.6% seats form the State Quota while 33.3% seats in each discipline are reserved for Management Quota. Admissions to all seats are made on the basis of merit of JEE/10+2 marks. </div>			
